---
/*
  DIY subpage 4 of 4 — How to Host a Closing Exhibition
  (/diy/host-an-exhibition). The last page in the read-in-order set.

  Sections, top to bottom (ticker, masthead, footer come from BaseLayout):
    1. Hero       — the M ❀ logo
    2. Heading    — cyan "* HOW TO HOST A CLOSING EXHIBITION" bar
    3. Body       — blue sub-headings, the offtime-outlets graphic, a Vimeo
                    embed of the Month Offline Gallery, and two photos
    4. Next       — loops back to the DIY guide index (no forward arrow)

  Underlined words use plain <u> for emphasis (same as the other subpages).
---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../../components/Hero.astro';
import SectionHeader from '../../components/SectionHeader.astro';
import NextLink from '../../components/NextLink.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="How to Host a Closing Exhibition — Month Offline" masthead="Month Offline > DIY Guide > Exhibition">
  <div class="sections">
    <!-- 1. Hero -->
    <Hero />

    <!-- 2. Heading -->
    <SectionHeader label="How to host a closing exhibition" />

    <!-- 3. Body -->
    <section class="card">
      <h3 class="label">What do ppl do with all their new free time?</h3>
      <p class="body">
        Month Offline is not just about what we're saying no to, but what we're
        inviting in. we always ask participants to consider choosing an Offtime
        Outlet for the month.
      </p>
      <p class="body">
        how might they want to spend their newfound free time? this is a
        permission slip to do that thing they've always wanted to do. keep it
        low-stakes and low-pressure! Offtime outlets come in many different
        shapes and sizes (including napping and spending more time with the
        kids). set aside some time to workshop ideas at each MO meetup.
      </p>

      <img
        class="card__photo"
        src="/images/exhibition-01.png"
        width="1200"
        height="1800"
        alt="A handwritten Offtime Outlets sign-up sheet listing participants and the slow pursuits they chose"
      />

      <h3 class="label">What's a community exhibition?</h3>
      <p class="body">
        the og Month Offline cohorts ended with a phone-free exhibition where
        participants shared their offtime projects with friends, family, and
        neighbors.
      </p>
      <p class="body">
        it's important to wrap things up with a public event so that ur cohort
        sparks a community conversation and more ppl are invited 2 join the
        attention liberation movement.
      </p>
      <p class="body">
        the goal is not to isolate participants in insular flip phone clubs, but
        to make our neighborhoods more enriching than our screens.
      </p>

      <!-- Vimeo embed of the Month Offline Gallery video. The responsive
           wrapper below keeps it at a 16:9 ratio at any width. -->
      <div class="video">
        <iframe
          src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1153751486"
          title="Month Offline Gallery"
          allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"
          allowfullscreen
        ></iframe>
      </div>

      <p class="body">
        the exhibition feels like a cross between a science fair, an open mic,
        and an art gallery.
      </p>
      <p class="body">
        spread the word by printing invitations and submitting to local
        newspapers or community calendars.
      </p>
      <p class="body">
        set up tables where ppl can showcase their projects. invite 2-3
        participants to share their experience during a ~20min panel and give
        guests plenty of time to ask their own questions. it's always a good
        time to listen to the trials and triumphs from the month-long challenge.
      </p>
      <p class="body">
        ppl leave feeling inspired reconsider their relationship to digital
        media and maybe even join a future MO cohort. find a way to collect
        contact information so u can follow up with guests after the event and
        grow ur scene!
      </p>

      <img
        class="card__photo"
        src="/images/exhibition-02.png"
        width="1500"
        height="1000"
        alt="A crowd gathered outdoors around the unrolled dumb scroll"
      />
      <img
        class="card__photo"
        src="/images/exhibition-03.png"
        width="1500"
        height="1000"
        alt="Guests viewing the dumb scroll displayed on a wall at the indoor exhibition"
      />
      <p class="caption">unrolling the dumb scroll</p>
    </section>

    <!-- 4. Next — last page loops back to the DIY guide index (no arrow). -->
    <NextLink label="DIY Guide" href="/diy" arrow={false} />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Standard body paragraph (Syne Mono). */
  .body {
    font-size: var(--size-body);
    line-height: var(--leading-body);
  }
  .body + .body {
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
  }

  /* Photos interspersed through the card. */
  .card__photo {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    margin: var(--space-3) 0;
  }

  /* Caption sitting snug beneath a photo (e.g. "unrolling the dumb scroll").
     The photo above carries the bottom gap, so pull the caption up to it. */
  .caption {
    font-size: var(--size-body);
    margin-top: calc(-1 * var(--space-2));
  }

  /* Responsive 16:9 wrapper for the Vimeo embed. The iframe fills it
     absolutely so the box keeps its ratio at any column width. */
  .video {
    position: relative;
    padding-top: 56.25%; /* 9 / 16 = 0.5625 */
    margin: var(--space-3) 0;
  }
  .video iframe {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    border: 0;
  }
</style>
